#. Type: boolean
#. Description
#. :sl1:
#: ../user-setup-udeb.templates:5001
msgid "Allow login as root?"
msgstr "Sireg tuqqna s root?"

#. Type: boolean
#. Description
#. :sl1:
#: ../user-setup-udeb.templates:5001
msgid ""
"If you choose not to allow root to log in, then a user account will be "
"created and given the power to become root using the 'sudo' command."
msgstr ""
"Ma yella tferneḍ ur tsirigeḍ ara anekcum i uẓar, ad yettwarnu umiḍan n "
"useqdac yerna ad yesɛu tazmert ad yuɣal d aẓar s useqdec n tladna \"sudo\"."

#. Type: password
#. Description
#. :sl1:
#: ../user-setup-udeb.templates:6001
msgid "Root password:"
msgstr "Awal n uɛeddi aẓar:"

#. Type: password
#. Description
#. :sl1:
#: ../user-setup-udeb.templates:6001
msgid ""
"Some account needs to be available with administrative super-user "
"privileges. The password for that account should be something that cannot be "
"guessed."
msgstr ""

#. Type: password
#. Description
#. :sl1:
#: ../user-setup-udeb.templates:6001
msgid ""
"To allow direct password-based access via the 'root' account, you can set "
"the password for that account here."
msgstr ""

#. Type: password
#. Description
#. :sl1:
#: ../user-setup-udeb.templates:6001
msgid ""
"Alternatively, you can lock the root account's password by leaving this "
"setting empty, and instead use the system's initial user account (which will "
"be set up in the next step) to gain administrative privileges. This will be "
"enabled for you by adding that initial user to the 'sudo' group."
msgstr ""

#. Type: password
#. Description
#. :sl1:
#: ../user-setup-udeb.templates:6001
msgid "Note: what you type here will be hidden (unless you select to show it)."
msgstr ""
"Tamawt: ayen ara taruḍ da ad yettwaffer (ala ma tferneḍ ad t-id-tessekneḍṭ)."

#. Type: password
#. Description
#. :sl1:
#. Type: password
#. Description
#. :sl1:
#: ../user-setup-udeb.templates:7001 ../user-setup-udeb.templates:14001
msgid "Re-enter password to verify:"
msgstr "Ales asekcem n wawal n uɛeddi i usenqed:"

#. Type: password
#. Description
#. :sl1:
#: ../user-setup-udeb.templates:7001
msgid ""
"Please enter the same root password again to verify that you have typed it "
"correctly."
msgstr ""
"Ttxil-k·m sekcem tikkelt-nniḍen awal uffir i teskecmeḍ tazwara i wakken ad "
"twaliḍ ma yella turiḍ-t swaswa."

#. Type: boolean
#. Description
#. :sl2:
#: ../user-setup-udeb.templates:8001
msgid "Create a normal user account now?"
msgstr "Rnu tura amiḍan n useqdac amagnu?"

#. Type: boolean
#. Description
#. :sl2:
#: ../user-setup-udeb.templates:8001
msgid ""
"It's a bad idea to use the root account for normal day-to-day activities, "
"such as the reading of electronic mail, because even a small mistake can "
"result in disaster. You should create a normal user account to use for those "
"day-to-day tasks."
msgstr ""
"Aseqdec n umiḍan aẓar i tigawin n yal ass timugna, am tɣuri n yimaylen "
"iliktṛunanen ula d tuccḍa tamecṭuḥt ad d-teglu s wuguren meqqren. Ilaq ad "
"ternuḍ amiḍan n useqdac amagnu i useqdec n tigawin-a n yal ass."

#. Type: boolean
#. Description
#. :sl2:
#: ../user-setup-udeb.templates:8001
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Note that you may create it later (as well as any additional account) by "
"typing 'adduser <username>' as root, where <username> is a username, like "
"'imurdock' or 'rms'."
msgstr ""
"Ẓer belli tzemreḍ ad t-ternuḍ mbeɛd (am yal amiḍan n zzyada) s tira n "
"'adduser <username>' d aẓar, anida <username> d isem n useqdac, am "
"'imurdock' neɣ 'rms'."

#. Type: string
#. Description
#. :sl1:
#: ../user-setup-udeb.templates:9001
msgid "Full name for the new user:"
msgstr "Isem ummid i useqdac amaynut:"

#. Type: string
#. Description
#. :sl1:
#: ../user-setup-udeb.templates:9001
msgid ""
"A user account will be created for you to use instead of the root account "
"for non-administrative activities."
msgstr ""
"Amiḍan n useqdac ad yettwarnu i kečč·kemm i wakken ad yettuseqdec deg ubdil "
"n umiḍan aẓar i tigawin ur nelli n unedbal."

#. Type: string
#. Description
#. :sl1:
#: ../user-setup-udeb.templates:9001
msgid ""
"Please enter the real name of this user. This information will be used for "
"instance as default origin for emails sent by this user as well as any "
"program which displays or uses the user's real name. Your full name is a "
"reasonable choice."
msgstr ""
"Ttxil-k·m sekcem isem n tidet n useqdac-a. Talɣut-a ad tettuseqdec d amedya "
"aɣbalu amezwer i yimaylen yettwaznen sɣur useqdac-a akked yal ahil ara d-"
"iseknen neɣ ad iseqdec isem aḥeqqani n useqdac. Isem-inek·inem ummid d afran "
"n ṣṣwab."

#. Type: string
#. Description
#. :sl1:
#: ../user-setup-udeb.templates:10001
msgid "Username for your account:"
msgstr "Isem n useqdac i umiḍan-inek·inem:"

#. Type: string
#. Description
#. :sl1:
#: ../user-setup-udeb.templates:10001
msgid ""
"Select a username for the new account. Your first name is a reasonable "
"choice. The username should start with a lower-case letter, which can be "
"followed by any combination of numbers and more lower-case letters."
msgstr ""
"Fren isem n useqdac i umiḍan amaynut. Isem-inek·inem amezwaru d lxetyaṛ n "
"ṣṣwab. Ẓer belli ismawen n useqdac ilaq ad bdun s usekkil ameẓẓyan, i "
"izemren ad d-ttuḍefren s yal tuddsa n yimḍanen d yisekkilen, daɣen ur ilaq "
"ara ad iɛeddi nnig n 32 yisekkilen."

#. Type: error
#. Description
#. :sl2:
#: ../user-setup-udeb.templates:11001
msgid "Invalid username"
msgstr "Isem n useqdac d urameɣtu"

#. Type: error
#. Description
#. :sl2:
#: ../user-setup-udeb.templates:11001
msgid ""
"The username you entered is invalid. Note that usernames must start with a "
"lower-case letter, which can be followed by any combination of numbers and "
"more lower-case letters, and must be no more than 32 characters long."
msgstr ""
"Isem n useqdac i teskecmeḍ d arameɣtu. Ẓer belli ismawen n useqdac ilaq ad "
"bdun s usekkil ameẓẓyan, i izemren ad d-ttuḍefren s yal tuddsa n yimḍanen d "
"yisekkilen, daɣen ur ilaq ara ad iɛeddi nnig n 32 yisekkilen."

#. Type: error
#. Description
#. :sl2:
#: ../user-setup-udeb.templates:12001
msgid "Reserved username"
msgstr "Isem n umseqdac yettuḥarren"

#. Type: error
#. Description
#. :sl2:
#: ../user-setup-udeb.templates:12001
msgid ""
"The username you entered (${USERNAME}) is reserved for use by the system. "
"Please select a different one."
msgstr ""
"Isem n useqdac i teskecmeḍ (${USERNAME}) yettuḥeṛṛ i useqdec sɣur unagraw. "
"Ttxil-k·m fren wayeḍ-nniḍen."

#. Type: password
#. Description
#. :sl1:
#: ../user-setup-udeb.templates:13001
msgid "Choose a password for the new user:"
msgstr "Fren awal uffir i useqdac amaynut:"

#. Type: password
#. Description
#. :sl1:
#: ../user-setup-udeb.templates:13001
msgid "Make sure to select a strong password that cannot be guessed."
msgstr ""
"Ur ttettu ara ad tferneḍ awal uɛeddi iǧehden, win ur yezmir yiwen ad t-id-"
"yaf."

#. Type: password
#. Description
#. :sl1:
#: ../user-setup-udeb.templates:14001
msgid ""
"Please enter the same user password again to verify you have typed it "
"correctly."
msgstr ""
"Ttxil-k·m sekcem tikkelt-nniḍen awal uffir i teskecmeḍ tazwara i wakken ad "
"twaliḍ ma turiḍ-t swaswa."

#. Type: error
#. Description
#. :sl2:
#: ../user-setup-udeb.templates:15001
msgid "Password input error"
msgstr "Tuccḍa n unekcum n wawal uffir"

#. Type: error
#. Description
#. :sl2:
#: ../user-setup-udeb.templates:15001
msgid "The two passwords you entered were not the same. Please try again."
msgstr ""
"I sin n wawalen uffiren i teskecmeḍ mačči yiwen-nsen. Ttxil-k·m ɛreḍ ticki."

#. Type: error
#. Description
#. :sl2:
#: ../user-setup-udeb.templates:16001
msgid "Empty password"
msgstr "Awal uffir d ilem"

#. Type: error
#. Description
#. :sl2:
#: ../user-setup-udeb.templates:16001
msgid ""
"You entered an empty password, which is not allowed. Please choose a non-"
"empty password."
msgstr ""
"Awal uffir i teskecmeḍ d ilem, d ayen ur nettusireg ara. Ttxil-k·m fren awal "
"uffir ur nelli d ilem."

#. Type: title
#. Description
#. :sl1:
#: ../user-setup-udeb.templates:17001
msgid "Set up users and passwords"
msgstr "Swel iseqdacen d wawalen uffiren"

#. Type: text
#. Description
#. finish-install progress bar item
#. :sl1:
#: ../user-setup-udeb.templates:18001
msgid "Setting users and passwords..."
msgstr "Asbadu n yiseqdac d wawalen uffiren..."
